We introduce salad , an open source toolbox that provides a uniﬁed implementa-1 tion of state-of-the-art methods for transfer learning, semi-supervised learning and 2 domain adaptation. In the ﬁrst release, we provide a framework for reproducing, 3 extending and combining research results of the past years, including model archi-4 tectures, loss functions and training algorithms. The toolbox along with ﬁrst bench-5 mark results and further resources is accessible at domainadaptation.org . 6